        "answer": "Daniel Erlandsson used Sabian AA and HH cymbals on Doomsday Machine. His setup paired the AA series — Sabian's professional bright-alloy line — for hi-hats and crash cymbals, with the HH series — darker, more tonally complex — for his ride. The 14\" AA Rock hi-hats provided fast, defined attack for rapid 16th-note patterns at Arch Enemy's tempos. AA crashes delivered the upper-frequency projection needed to cut through Michael Amott's layered guitar production. The HH 22\" ride introduced tonal contrast in groove-oriented passages where the brighter crash character would be too aggressive. Andy Sneap's production captured this cymbal setup with disciplined overhead microphone placement and EQ choices, preserving the natural tonal character of each cymbal. The same fundamental cymbal approach (later refined with the AAX/HHX series) continued to define Erlandsson's Arch Enemy work for the rest of his career."
