        "question": "Why is Anthems of Rebellion considered Angela Gossow's first full Arch Enemy album?",
        "answer": "Anthems of Rebellion (2003) is considered Angela Gossow's first full album with Arch Enemy because it was the first record where she was part of the band's creative process from the beginning — the songwriting, arrangements, and recording all developed with Gossow as a fully integrated member of the lineup. Wages of Sin (2002) was her debut as Arch Enemy's vocalist, but the band had already begun development of that material before she joined; the Wages sessions adapted existing material to her presence. Anthems of Rebellion was built around the Angela Gossow–era Arch Enemy identity from the outset, making it the first complete creative statement of the era that would define the band for the next decade. For the broader Arch Enemy and Erlandsson context: [Daniel Erlandsson at MetalForge](/drummer/daniel-erlandsson)."
